    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "identifier": "media-2929809",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "2929809",
                "title": "Figure 1",
                "abstract": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "A cone and its properties "
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A cone defines the surface of a solid whose base is a circle and whose side surface tapers to a point centered above its base. A frustum also has a circular base and tapered sides but has a circular top, similar to a cone cut off below its apex."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Define the size of the cone’s base in the x- and z-axis dimensions of its local coordinate space with its "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scncone/1523198-bottomradius"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property, and its extent in the y-axis dimension with its "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scncone/1523219-height"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property. Create a cone that tapers to a point by setting its "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scncone/1524240-topradius"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property to zero, or a frustum that tapers (or expands) to a circular top by setting the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scncone/1524240-topradius"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property to a different value."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To position and orient a cone in a scene, attach it to the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnnode/1407966-geometry"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property of an "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnnode"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Control the level of detail with the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scncone/1523942-radialsegmentcount"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scncone/1524113-heightsegmentcount"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " properties. A higher radial segment count creates a smoother curve for the cone’s circular sides. A higher segment count in either direction produces more vertices, which can improve rendering quality for certain lighting models or custom shader effects, but at a cost to rendering performance."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A cone geometry may contain two or three "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scngeometryelement"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " objects, corresponding to its outer surface, its base and its top (or base only or top only, if the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scncone/1524240-topradius"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " or "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scncone/1523198-bottomradius"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property is zero). SceneKit can render each element using a different material. For details, see the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scngeometry/1523472-materials"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property in "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scngeometry"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
